Until it emerged as the unanimous all around resolution of all the delegates who came here, not a dissenting voice. They call upon the president to say you have done a good work, you have turned around an economy which was comatose, we had no currency, we were a pariah state. We were spending all our money on social welfare. Now the economy is vibrant, we are the fastest growing, we have sinews of the economy which points to affect that the middle incomes goal status is achievable, this is why they want the president to continue and they have appointed the president to continue. Thats what they did; they called upon the president. Of course the president is a constitutionalist; he still sticks to the position that he will save two terms, but it does not dispense the wish of the democratic people, that the president could save or should save longer than that.

What becomes of it, we are going to make sure that all the constitutional aspects to make this resolution realisable, are addressed, and this is the call by the conference. They not only passed the resolution, but they said mechanisms should be instituted to make sure that this resolution is realized. So this is the goal of the party. As to what will happen 2028, its up to the president. It is choice. He is a constitutionalist and he is a free man. He may want to comply with the resolution or he may not want to comply with the resolution, but that is another thing, because its a choice. In any event, in any way, in 2028, will always be on the calendar of God. The time will come to decide on that matter. For the time being, we have work to do, which is to deliver a vibrant economy, which will make Zimbabwe the shining star of Africa. We are doing well on the African stage. We are doing well on the global stage. This president is delivering on all those aspects; ticking every box of virtues in terms of what is doing for Zimbabwe. So let the man do his job. If it aint broke, dont fix it.

